cs.DB, cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.SE 

This paper deals with problems related to databases, specifically in the context of materialized views and dependencies. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DB (Databases). The paper also discusses security-related measures, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of algorithms and complexity analysis indicates that it could also fit into cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper mentions access control policies and auditing, which could place it in cs.SE (Software Engineering).
